## Walk-Brass: The God-Machine

The **Numidium** (also called **Walk-Brass**, **Anumidium**, or the **Brass God**) is a colossal Dwemer automaton designed not as a mere weapon of war but as a **vehicle for the divine ascension** of an entire people. Hundreds — or even thousands — of meters tall, this construction of metal and tonal magic represents the ultimate realization of Dwemer philosophy: the denial of the gods' existence and the creation of divinity through pure reason.

## Design and Dwemer Philosophy

### The Rejection of the Divine

The Dwemer were unique among the peoples of Nirn: they **denied the existence of gods** as other races understood them. To them, the Aedra and Daedra were merely exploitable phenomena, not entities worthy of worship. Their philosophy — **Tonal Architecture** — held that reality was made of manipulable vibrations.

### Kagrenac's Project

**Kagrenac**, the most brilliant of the tonal architects, designed the Numidium as the ultimate proof of this philosophy:

- If gods are only accumulations of belief and energy...
- And if the Heart of Lorkhan contains pure divine energy...
- Then one can **construct** a god, and that god will prove that divinity is just a mechanism

The Numidium was to be the **god of the Dwemer** — an artificial deity that would grant them immortality and transcendence, not through faith, but through engineering.

## Architecture and Function

### Physical Structure

The Numidium is a bipedal golem of titanic proportions:
- **Estimated height**: between 300 and 1,000 meters depending on the source
- **Materials**: enchanted Dwemer alloys, tonal focusing crystals, ebony framework
- **Weaponry**: no conventional weapons — its power lies in its very nature

### The Principle of Tonal Negation

The Numidium's true weapon is neither projectile nor blade. It is the **NO** — Tonal Negation. When the Numidium is activated and focused on a target, it does not destroy it: it **negates its existence**. It pronounces, at the metaphysical scale, a "NO" so absolute that reality conforms to the assertion.

In practical terms:
- Entire armies cease to have ever existed
- Fortifications are retroactively erased
- Time itself fractures around its activation (Dragon Break)

### The Power Source: The Heart of Lorkhan

To function, the Numidium requires a divine energy source. Kagrenac designed it to be powered by the **Heart of Lorkhan** — the heart of the creator god, buried beneath Red Mountain. This attempted activation caused the disappearance of the Dwemer in 1E 700.

## The Incomplete Numidium

After the disappearance of the Dwemer, the Numidium lay inert beneath Red Mountain — a hollow colossus, without a divine soul to animate it. For millennia it remained an archaeological mystery, too dangerous to study, too powerful to ignore.

The **Tribunal** knew of its existence but could not activate it: the Heart of Lorkhan now powered their own divinity.

## Reconstruction by Tiber Septim

### The Deal with Vivec

In **2E 896**, **Tiber Septim** (Talos) sought to conquer the Aldmeri Dominion — the last power resisting his Empire. Vivec, ever pragmatic, offered him a deal: the Numidium and Kagrenac's plans in exchange for Morrowind's autonomy (the Armistice Treaty).

### The Mantella

Without the Heart of Lorkhan, Tiber Septim needed an alternative power source. According to the **Arcturian Heresy**, he used the **Mantella** — a gem containing the soul of **Zurin Arctus** (the Imperial Underking, possibly identical to Wulfharth/Ysmir). The extraction of this soul was an act of betrayal:

| Element | Detail |
|---------|--------|
| **The Mantella** | Soul gem containing the spirit of a Shezarrine |
| **Zurin Arctus** | Betrayed Imperial mage, became the Underking |
| **Wulfharth** | Resurrected Nordic High King, possible alternative source of the soul |

### The Conquest of the Dominion

Tiber Septim activated the rebuilt Numidium — renamed **Anumidium** — against the Aldmeri Dominion. The effect was devastating and immediate: the High Elves capitulated. A single deployment was enough to break the resistance of an entire continent.

## The Warp in the West (3E 417)

### The Dragon Break

Centuries later, the Numidium was reactivated in the Iliac Bay region. The event, known as the **Warp in the West** or the **Dragon Break of the Iliac Bay**, caused a **Dragon Break** — a temporal fracture in which several contradictory realities coexisted simultaneously before merging.

Six mutually exclusive outcomes all occurred at the same time:
- Daggerfall conquered the region
- Wayrest conquered the region
- Sentinel conquered the region
- Orsinium was restored
- The Underking recovered the Mantella
- The Empire took direct control

The Numidium was ultimately deactivated (or destroyed), and the Mantella was released.

## Metaphysical Significance

The Numidium is not a mere giant automaton. It is an **embodied philosophical declaration**:

- It proves that divinity can be **manufactured**, undermining the entire theological framework of Tamriel
- Its power of Negation threatens the **Godhead's Dream** itself — if it negated enough reality, it could theoretically "awaken" the Amaranth
- It is the ultimate expression of Dwemer atheism: a god built to prove that gods are just machines

The Numidium remains, even inactive, one of the most dangerous objects in the Aurbis — a metaphysical bomb capable of fracturing time and erasing existence.
